          "question_html": "The milk and water in two vessels A and B are in the ratio 4:3 and 2:3 respectively. In what ratio the liquids in both the vessels be mixed to obtain a new mixture in vessel c consisting half milk and half water?",
          "option_1": "A) 8:3",
          "option_2": "B) 6:7",
          "option_3": "C) 7:5",
          "option_4": "D) 11:7",
          "answer": "C) 7:5",
          "explanation_html": "<div class='ansDivBox' id='answer13080'><a class='box-head' href='javascript:showans('13080','Alligation or Mixture')'><i class='icon-minus'></i> </a><span class='highlight'>Answer:</span> C) 7:5         <br/><br/><span class='highlight'>Explanation:</span><br/> <p>Milk in 1-litre mixture of A = 4/7 litre. </p><p>Milk in 1-litre mixture of B = 2/5 litre. </p><p>Milk in 1-litre mixture of C = 1/2 litre.</p><p> </p><p>By rule of alligation we have required ratio X:Y   </p><p>   X                  :                 Y  </p><p>  4/7                                2/5  </p><p>                                 /</p><p>              (Mean ratio)<br/>                   (1/2) </p><p>           /                      </p><p> (1/2 – 2/5)     :       (4/7 – 1/2)  </p><p>    1/10                      1/1 4 </p><p> </p><p>So Required ratio = X : Y = 1/10 : 1/14 = <strong>7:5</strong></p></div>"
