          "question_html": "In what ratio must a merchant mix two varieties of oils worth Rs. 60/kg and Rs. 65/kg, so that by selling the mixture at Rs. 68.20/kg, he may gain 10% ?",
          "option_1": "A) 2:3",
          "option_2": "B) 4:3",
          "option_3": "C) 3:4",
          "option_4": "D) 3:2",
          "answer": "D) 3:2",
          "explanation_html": "<div class='ansDivBox' id='answer12754'><a class='box-head' href='javascript:showans('12754','Alligation or Mixture')'><i class='icon-minus'></i> </a><span class='highlight'>Answer:</span> D) 3:2         <br/><br/><span class='highlight'>Explanation:</span><br/> <p>Let he mixes the oils in the ratio = x : y</p><p>Then, the cost price of the oils = 60x + 65y</p><p>Given selling price = Rs. 68.20</p><p>=&gt; Selling price = 68.20(x+y)</p><p>Given profit = 10% = SP - CP</p><p>=&gt; 10/100 (60x + 65y) = 68.20(x+y)-(60x + 65y)</p><p>=&gt; 6x + 6.5y = 8.20x + 3.20y</p><p>=&gt;2.2x = 3.3y</p><p>=&gt; x : y = 3 : 2</p></div>"
